# Astro + i18n Patterns

## Bilingual Rule

Every user-facing string needs EN and FR variants.

```ts
// Common UI strings — use translation hook
import { useTranslations } from '@/i18n/translations';
const t = useTranslations(locale); // locale: 'en' | 'fr'
t.nav.services // returns the right language

// Page-specific text — use isFr boolean
const isFr = locale === 'fr';
const title = isFr ? 'Titre Français' : 'English Title';
```

Bilingual data fields: `name`/`frName`, `slug`/`frSlug`, `features`/`frFeatures`, `faqs`/`frFaqs`, `description`/`frDescription`.

## Page Structure Pattern

```astro
---
export function getStaticPaths() {
  return [{ params: { locale: 'en' } }, { params: { locale: 'fr' } }];
}
const { locale } = Astro.params as { locale: 'en' | 'fr' };
const isFr = locale === 'fr';
const altLocale = isFr ? 'en' : 'fr';

// Build schema array using src/seo/ generators
import { getBreadcrumbSchema } from '@/seo';
const schema = [breadcrumbSchema, otherSchema];
---
<PageLayout title={...} locale={locale} schema={schema} heroTitle={...} alternateUrls={[...]}>
  <!-- content -->
</PageLayout>
```

## Programmatic Pages (880 combos)

Both patterns render the same content for different SEO entry points:
- `src/pages/[locale]/area/[locationSlug]/[serviceSlug].astro` — canonical, location-first
- `src/pages/[locale]/services/[serviceSlug]/[locationSlug].astro` — service-first (alternate canonical)

`getStaticPaths()` cross-joins all `locales × locations × services` — add location/service to their data files and pages appear automatically.

## SEO Schemas

```ts
import { getBreadcrumbSchema, getLocationServiceSchema, getFAQSchema } from '@/seo';

// Always pass via PageLayout's schema prop — never inject <script type="application/ld+json"> manually
const schema = [
  getLocationServiceSchema({ service, location, locale }),
  getBreadcrumbSchema(breadcrumbs, locale),
  ...(service.faqs.length ? [getFAQSchema(service.faqs, locale)] : []),
];
```

Available generators: `getLocalBusinessSchema`, `getServiceSchema`, `getFAQSchema`, `getBreadcrumbSchema`, `getLocationServiceSchema`, `getHowToSchema`, `getReviewSchema`, `getFounderSchema`.

## hreflang Alternate URLs

```ts
import { hreflangUrl } from '@/lib/utils';
// Pass to PageLayout:
alternateUrls={[{ locale: altLocale, url: `https://allstarcleaning.ca/${altLocale}/services/` }]}
```

## i18n Middleware

`src/middleware.ts` exempts `/keystatic/*` and `/api/keystatic/*` from locale routing. All other routes get locale-prefixed. `/` → `/en/`. Add new API-like routes to the exemption list if they should bypass i18n.
